Step1 --- Create a virtual environment: 'python -m venv myenv'

Step2 --- Activate the virtual environment : 'source myenv/bin/activate'

Step3 --- After installing django and djangofranework ,Create a new Django project: 'django-admin startproject myproject.'
Step4 --- Add Django REST framework to INSTALLED_APPS: Add Django REST framework to your project's INSTALLED_APPS setting in the settings.py file.
          You can do this by adding 'rest_framework' to the list of installed apps.

Step5 --- Create a new app: 'python manage.py startapp myapp.'
Step6 --- Add the app to INSTALLED_APPS: to project's 'INSTALLED_APPS' setting in the 'settings.py' file.

Step7 --- Define your model : 'models.py'
Step8 --- Finally, start the development server by running 'python manage.py runserver'.
           You can now access your API by visiting 'http://localhost:8000/' in your web browser.
